review_blob: From a bottle at the brewdungeon. A lot of great barrel on the nose but the base beer still shines through. As with the base beer the palate is a bit lighter than my liking. Nonetheless a great beer and I cant wait for the other beers coming out of that dungeon.
beer_name: Rooie Dop Double Oatmeal Stout Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: If you want a coffee porter this one delivers. In your face coffee aroma and flavors. A bit heavy on the carbonation and lighter on the palate than I would have liked but after all this is a 6.5% coffee porter and NOT a RIS.

A beer that does almost everything right. Great fruity and hoppy aroma, flavors follow the nose in a briliant way. Good moutfeel, easy to drink despite the 9.1%.

Readily available to me and Im so happy for it.

Nice looking, one finger foam, great roasted flavors, lacking a little bit on the palate but not in a disturbing way.
Great brewery!

From a 750 ml bottle. 
Loads of sweetness on the nose. Some medicinal qualities.
Flavors are sweet and spicey. Grows on me as I drink.
medium body and carbonation goes down smooth with a little burn.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Bold nose and Great flavors but a light body and too much carbonation keeps this one from being stellar.

Had a bottle with Jeff. Thanks Jeff. Loved the look of it. The aroma almost a little burned coffee, a little bourbon and some hints of vanilla. The flavor exploded in my mouth! Fantastic! Extremely smooth, nice bitterness and a very nice vanilla aftertaste. One of the greatest stouts Ive ever had

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: 0.5 liter bottle. The best discovery of this summer for me. HAs all the greatness of a fantastic Weisbier. Fruity banana... yeasty and hops, hops and hops. Makes me wish it was summer again. Great!!!

750 ml bottle. Nice hoppy aroma. Hints of fruit and according to Jeff also Kool Aid red cherry. Pours hazy caramel. Not the taste explosion I was hoping for but not too bad. Bitter aftertaste not too complex but just harsh.

Small bottle @ home. No carbonation. Winelike mouthfeel. There is some barrel flavour present not as distinct as the other barrel aged versions which I prefer. A little carbonation on this one would have made a difference maybe...
beer_name: De Molen Hel & Verdoemenis Bordeaux BA
